As of **March 10, 2025**, Salesforce’s latest available Form 10-K reported **$8.50 billion** of total debt face value (outstanding principal) as of January 31, 2025. This included **$1.00 billion** of 2028 Senior Sustainability Notes.

**Calculation:**

\[
\$8.50\text{ billion} - \$1.00\text{ billion} = \boxed{\$7.50\text{ billion}}
\]

Therefore, the **face value of Salesforce’s debt excluding its sustainability notes was $7.50 billion**. This is the face/principal amount, not the carrying value; the corresponding carrying value excluding those notes was $7.438 billion.

